From 7b9c7fc14559ac322b1b94e07280be6bc5270354 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Florian Fuchs <fuchsfl@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 04 Jul 2026 22:16:15 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] video fix

It looks like the output auto-detection paths were non-functional, since
initial git commit and it was hardcoded to VGA and PAL output. Which is
sad for composite, TV and our good NTSC friends all over the world. Let's
give them output as well.

Signed-off-by: Florian Fuchs <fuchsfl@gmail.com>
---
Digging into the tglx/history.git repository got me this commit as the
one that replaced -1 autodetection with VGA only, with no further
explanation.

commit 434502754f2273c6664d318bd9ffac636a214611
Author: Andrew Morton <akpm@osdl.org>
Date:   Sun Jan 18 18:05:04 2004 -0800

    [PATCH] SH Merge
    
    From: Paul Mundt <lethal@linux-sh.org>
    
    Here's a rather large update for SH (this is a bit large mainly since a
    number of things have piled up, and Linus didn't want any of this during
    feature freeze time). All of these changes are specific to the SH platform,
    and as such, shouldn't effect any other platforms.


diff --git a/drivers/video/fbdev/pvr2fb.c b/drivers/video/fbdev/pvr2fb.c
index 3f6384e631b1..da748e377716 100644
--- a/drivers/video/fbdev/pvr2fb.c
+++ b/drivers/video/fbdev/pvr2fb.c
@@ -171,8 +171,8 @@ static const struct fb_var_screeninfo pvr2_var = {
        .vmode =        FB_VMODE_NONINTERLACED,
 };
 
-static int cable_type = CT_VGA;
-static int video_output = VO_VGA;
+static int cable_type = -1;
+static int video_output = -1;
 
 static int nopan = 0;
 static int nowrap = 1;
